How do I enable BitLocker without TPM?
Double-click the “Require additional authentication at startup” option in the right pane. Select “Enabled” at the top of the window, and ensure the “Allow BitLocker without a compatible TPM (requires a password or a startup key on a USB flash drive)” checkbox is enabled here. Click “OK” to save your changes.{ source google}
